Paramedics say the man has been rushed to hospital after being wounded in the arm. JOHANNESBURG - A man has been shot and wounded in an attempted hijacking in Sandton. Paramedics say the man has been rushed to hospital after being wounded in the arm on Friday afternoon. Netcare 911's Tebogo Magoro said: “The exact circumstances are not yet known to our paramedics, but local authorities were on scene. The incident and the preceding event will form part of the police investigation.”